linux file system:
when we install the linux operating systems linux offers many file systems such as Ext,Ext2,Ext3...
linux also supports 100 file systems ,including some very old ones as well as some of the newest
each of these file system types uses its own metadata structures to define how the data is stored and accessed.
 
  */:root directory(base of the file sysyem). 
 
  /bin:executable programs.
  
  /boot:linux kernel and boot ladder.

  /dev:special device files.
  
  /etc:system configuration files.
  
  /home:home directories of all users.
  
  /lib:library files for programs.